import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='precipitation', by='location', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation across the locations?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(data.groupby('year')['temp_range'].mean(), label='Average Temperature Range')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature Range (°C)')
    plt.title('How does the temperature range vary across the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['precipitation'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wind and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    
    data['temp_max'].plot.hist(alpha=0.5, bins=30, label='Temp Max', ax=ax)
    data['temp_min'].plot.hist(alpha=0.5, bins=30, label='Temp Min', ax=ax)
    
    ax.axvline(data['temp_max'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean Temp Max: {data['temp_max'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['temp_min'].mean(), color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean Temp Min: {data['temp_min'].mean():.2f}")
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of temperature max and temperature min?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Temperature")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().unstack()
    ax = weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('How does the weather vary across the locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title='Weather', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
